      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three refinement levels (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~210k elements, fine: ~520k elements) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for stiffness QoI = 0.31%, yield force QoI = 0.48%, force at 40 mm = 0.62%. All GCI values < 1%. Production mesh (medium refinement) selected for computational efficiency. Achieved level 3 (formal GCI-based error estimation) exceeds required level 2 (mesh sensitivity study)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
