      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/solver-error-level1",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static analysis uses Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual convergence tolerance of 1×10⁻⁴ and displacement residual 1×10⁻⁵. All load steps converged within 15 iterations. Energy balance checked post-solution; artificial energy < 0.1% of total internal energy, confirming no hourglassing or contact penetration artifacts. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1 for this factor at MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, material assignments, and load application was performed by a second analyst at each of the three ensemble organizations. Discrepancies identified during review (minor contact pair assignments) were resolved prior to production runs. Analysis procedure documented in a controlled simulation plan (SP-2023-NC-001) with step-by-step instructions. Cross-organization ensemble comparison serves as an additional use-error check. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-form-level2",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) with isotropic hardening plasticity (σ_y=880 MPa) used for screw and rod. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate modeled as linear elastic (E=1.17 GPa) consistent with ASTM F1717 standard block geometry. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) between screw-rod interface. Bilinear material model validated against coupon tensile data (R²=0.997). Model form assumptions documented and justified against published literature for F1717 constructs. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from certified CMM measurements of production screws (n=5, tolerance ±0.01 mm). Material properties sourced from certified mill certificates and supplemented by in-house tensile coupon testing (n=3 per batch). Torque preload on set screw measured experimentally (mean 4.0 N·m, SD 0.15 N·m) and applied as bolt pretension in FEA. Probabilistic sensitivity analysis (Latin hypercube, n=500 samples) identifies screw root diameter and UHMWPE modulus as dominant inputs; uncertainty contributions quantified and propagated to QoI uncertainty budget. Achieved level 3 (probabilistic input characterization) exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested: n=6 at Lab 1 (FDA CDRH) and n=5 at Lab 2 (DePuy Synthes). All constructs assembled from the same production lot (Lot 2022-NC-7.5-A). Sample size provides 80% power to detect 10% difference in mean stiffness at α=0.05 (power analysis documented in test plan TP-2022-F1717-NC). CMM verification of each test specimen confirmed dimensional conformance. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single test condition (ASTM F1717 standard configuration: 10° angulation, compression-bending, displacement rate 5 mm/min, ambient temperature 23±2°C). Only one loading mode evaluated; fatigue and torsion conditions not included in this COU. Achieved level 1 is below required level 2; this known gap is acknowledged in the decision record and accepted because (a) ASTM F1717 is the regulatory-standard test condition, (b) compression-bending is the worst-case loading mode for this construct geometry per published biomechanical literature, and (c) model influence is Medium with physical testing serving as the primary regulatory evidence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/equivalency-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs directly correspond to experimentally measured parameters: screw geometry from CMM data, UHMWPE block modulus from compression testing of surrogate material, applied displacement boundary condition matching test machine crosshead displacement. Set-screw torque preload applied identically in model and experiment (4.0 N·m). Friction coefficient validated against dedicated pull-out test series. Parameter-by-parameter equivalency table documented in simulation plan SP-2023-NC-001 Appendix B. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/output-comparison-level2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for all three QoIs using both percentage difference (< 10% acceptance bound) and normalized error metric E/uval (< 1.96 acceptance bound). Uncertainty budget for E/uval computation includes: experimental measurement uncertainty (load cell ±0.5%, displacement ±0.1 mm), inter-specimen variability (pooled SD across both labs), and FEA numerical uncertainty (GCI-based). All three QoIs pass both criteria: stiffness (4.2%, E/uval=0.84), yield force (6.7%, E/uval=1.12), force at 40 mm (8.9%, E/uval=1.55). Ensemble agreement across three FEA implementations further corroborates results. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs selected (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the standard outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical performance: stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column, yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation, and force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to catastrophic failure. QoI selection justified in the model description document (MDD-2022-NC-001) with explicit linkage to failure modes identified in device FMEA. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
